-- SHADOW-SEMANTICS cell D16: the OPPOSITE arity direction to d13 — the METHOD's
-- arity (1) is now SMALLER than the STANDALONE's (2) (issue #410).
--
-- d13 covers method 2 / standalone 1; this covers method 1 / standalone 2, which
-- exercises the other side of the route-derived arity. Pre-fix the lift built a
-- 1-arity closure around a body calling the 2-arity standalone; post-fix
-- methValArity reads the standalone's arity off the RLocal route, so the closure
-- is arity 2 and `f 1 2` is a saturated direct call.
--
-- The result is annotated `Int` for the same reason as d13: isolate the emitter
-- arity lie from the separate unannotated requirement-route bug (d14), which bites
-- this shape too (unannotated, println's Display dict is emitted NULL and the
-- binary segfaults even though no list is involved).
-- Expected: check/run/build all accept and print 3.
interface Sz a where
  size : a -> Int

size : Int -> Int -> Int
size n m = n + m

main =
  let r = let f = size in f 1 2 : Int
  println r
